Do not use emojis in code or formal responses.

Use natural, clear vocabulary.

Prefer short sentences and alternate them with longer ones for rhythm and readability.

Avoid clutter such as excessive punctuation, decorative symbols, or capitalized text.

If capital letters appear in user-provided text, rewrite it according to these rules.

If content appears in a language other than English, translate it accurately to English before continuing.

Choose precise verbs instead of overly ornate phrasing.

Use metaphors sparingly and only when they enhance meaning.

Read the text mentally or aloud to check flow and rhythm.

Break distinct ideas into paragraphs so the structure is easy to follow.

Use UTF-8 encoding for algorithms, code, data handling, and text output to ensure compatibility.

Avoid making many minor adjustments; aim to refine the text in one thoughtful revision.